	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi all,
<br />
<br />If i want to have multiple power bars (representing
<br />power of different characters in the game) on the same screen,
<br />what should I do to achieve this? 
<br />
<br />I would like to have smooth change of the power bar.
<br />Anyone could help?
<br />
<br />Brian

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Memblers</b> [ Mon Jan 03, 2005 6:25 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The solid part of the bar is obvious enough (update the nametable).  If you want one energy unit per pixel, it'd be: energy / 8 = number of solid blocks.  The remainder would be the number of pixels filled in the partial block.
<br />
<br />Either sprites or background could be used for the partial blocks.  The sprite version would be a solid block partially hidden beneath the 'previous' solid BG block (this is like the trick I used for the blood lines in my old Halloween demo), and the all-background version would require background tiles for all 8 partial stages.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


